Defendant Jonathan T Storck in court with Attorney Jeffrey Jacob De La Rosa.   ADA Monica Hall appears for the State of Wisconsin.

Mr. Stork waives his right to Preliminary Hearing; the Court accepts this waiver and binds him over for Trial.

Arraignment:
--service of Information admitted, reading waived

Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " Guilty " entered; factual basis stipulated; the Court accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

--Atty. De La Rosa indicates that the restitution amounts requested are accurate

--Atty. De La Rosa indicates the ability to pay is for the restitution to Progressive Insurance
--Arguments given by Atty. De La Rosa
--The Court questions Mr. Storck
--The Court makes factual findings
--The Court concludes that Mr. Storck DOES have the ability to pay the restitution to Progressive Insurance over an 18 month Probation period.

Sentencing arguments given by Counsel

The Court withholds sentence, and places Defendant on Probation for 18 months, with conditions:
--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with recommended treatment per Agent
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment or  counseling as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--to attempt to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program as approved by the Agent
--maintain absolute sobriety
--no presence in bars or taverns
--monthly testing for illegal drug use
--to provide a DNA sample upon demand
--to pay costs of $268 plus the $250 DNA surcharge
--to pay restitution in the amount of $1000 to Joshua Storck pursuant to 973.20(6)
--to pay restitution in the amount of $7,223.31 to Progressive Insurance (claim #15-4129122) 24322 Network Place, Chicago, IL 60673-1243
--10% restitution surcharge

The Court grants Expungement upon successful completion of Probation
